Virgin Active opens again on Monday. But the country's largest gym chain says it's disappointed with the 50-person limit imposed. #eNCA spoke to Virgin Active's chief marketing and technology officer, Nikki Cockcroft. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Virgin Active says it is ready to open its doors again on Monday. The country's largest gym chain says it will adapt to government's regulation of a 50-person limit. SA lockdown: Gyms flex their muscles "During the last 5 months, we have really prepared our gyms. "We have spaced our equipment and put in all the cleaning and hygiene protocols," said Virgin Active's chief marketing and technology officer, Nikki Cockcroft. Under lockdown level-two regulations, gyms and fitness centers have the green light to reopen.